    <note>Yang(2) Cunzhong [7401] He was a general at beginning of Southern Song. His father, Zhen [4040], entered the civil service through the mingjing exam. He learned military strategy from his grandfather Zongmin [4055], who died in battle against the Jin in 1128. Tan(2) 's [2025] father, Zhang(1) Ji(3)'s [7151] grandfather-in-law. His second son, Xie [4043], was Gongbu shilang for a brief period in 1159. His wife was Zhao(1) Taizong's [9002] seventh generation descendant. CHECK Sun Di's funerary inscription for wife, born Zhao, who died in 1150 at age 44). XNYL, 181.6b, 10a; Liu Yizhi, WJ, 48.1a, 10a; Lu You, WJ, 36.3b; Jiajing Guo XZ. CBD, 4, 3163-4.</note>
